76561198202051597,Recommended,262410,29661456,Posted: 2 February,all,lilshrimp01,"Not going to lie- this is a pretty awesome game. At first I was skeptical due to the fact that you have to pay 50 dollars to buy all the guns unlocked, plus 10 dollars for the gun range. Because of this I thought the ""free"" really meant ""demo,"" which after playing the tutorial I found out it wasn't a ""pay to get more play"" game. Instead, you gain experience from doing certain things to the original gun you get such as disassembling, assembling, and time trials. These activities merit you experience with which you can aquire more guns. The second gun you get, the Colt, is about 2,000 experience, so after you do a few tasks for the tutorial you will have just enough experience to buy the Colt. The unlocking in this game is sort of like a tech tree where as you can't unlock more guns until you unlock the previous gun, and as you get higher in the tree it branches off. For instance you unlock the Colt, then the MP5, then that branches off to the Bretta or Tech 9. After you complete certain tasks you gain the power to shoot the gun, customize the gun, and watch it in x-ray and slow motion to see all the working parts. To sum everything all up, if you love guns and love learning more about them, this is the game for you!"
