,Recommended,262410,29814533,Posted: 9 February,all,██████,"The game's objective is easily outlined and aptly described by its title:You have a gun. You take the gun apart. You put the gun back together.It begins with a field strip. Then a disassembly. Then a reassembly. The game holds your hand at that stage, so you get a rough idea of where you're going.Then, after getting a run through how to work the gun, you get the Game modes, playing against the clock and your own ham-fistedness, trying to achieve a high score.New guns are unlocked via experience points, which are effectively available infinitely, and with credits. A single credit is earned when you first reach the top spot in the leadboards for a gun. This means that there is a finite amount of credits to be had, and their spending should be well-considered.Of course, there's another way to get credits and EXP, and that's where the microtransactions come in. I've not personally done this, but you can buy credits and EXP for real money. It is not, however, necessary.As for the gameplay itself, it is for the most part fairly solid, though often overly particular about which bits can be taken off the gun at which point in time. Figuring this out is solely a matter of repetition, yet often a source of frustration. It's an incredibly grindy game, no two ways about it.And I, personally, adore it. After a while I decided I'd be a good little blighter and give the devs some money as a show of support, so I bought the car pack."
,Recommended,262410,29787348,Posted: 8 February,all,Renny,"I enjoyed it for around an hour. It is not my type of game, since it requires you to remember a lot. However it doesn't mean that the game is bad, it is really good for a free to play game. I can't understand the hate going around for the micro-transactions, but I guess that I didn't play the game enought to realise that yet.In overall I'm not going to place a '10/10' rating, instead I will list few good things :-It is fun to play for a certain amount of time (at least for me)-I like the option of uploading the skins you made on a specific gun instantly to the workshop-There are a lot of guns to 'play' with-In the workshop you can download people's own guns and perform the same actions, as with the in game one's.-This game is clearly made for people who like to grind (I like to do so, but as I mentioned not my type)Thank you for your attention!"
